Statements/Instructions/Operator/Operation (instance of)/Operand: See intro of part 4.
* Statement: in the source code. Atomic element for code selection. May have side effect (as opposed to expressions). 
* Instruction: ISA (with the differentiation depending on the format or not) element
* Operator: arithmetic part of the instruction
* Operation: atomic part of the assembly code
* Operation instance: dynamic instance of it during the execution (P. Feautrier's Operation)

Store/Load/Use/Def/Assignment/Operand:
* Store, Load: always for memory accesses
* For scalars, talk about assignments/definitions/uses

Dominator tree. Not dominance tree.